OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1778547792
OL,3,CHouseholds to slam brakes on spending
OL,4,Cas Iran war sends cost surging, warns
OL,5,CEY
OL,7,FConsumer spending is set to pull back
OL,8,Fsharply as an inflation spike caused
OL,9,Fby the Iran war takes its toll on
OL,10,Fhousehold finances and the wider
OL,11,Feconomy, according to a report.
OL,13,FEY's economic outlook shows UK
OL,14,Fconsumer spending growth will grind
OL,15,Falmost to a halt, at a predicted 0.3%
OL,16,Ffor 2026, down from the 0.9% predicted
OL,17,Fbefore the conflict.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1778547792
OL,3,CHouseholds to slam brakes on spending
OL,4,Cas Iran war sends cost surging, warns
OL,5,CEY
OL,7,FDiscretionary spending will bare the
OL,8,Fbrunt of the hit, with consumer-facing
OL,9,Fcompanies set to be impacted, while
OL,10,Fthe energy price shock will wreak
OL,11,Fhavoc on manufacturing and industrial
OL,12,Ffirms, EY said.
OL,14,FIt has joined other forecasters in
OL,15,Fpredicting sharply slower growth this
OL,16,Fyear following the outbreak of war in
OL,17,Fthe Middle East, predicting output
OL,18,Fwill grow by 0.8%, down from the 1.3%
OL,19,Fthe UK was on track to notch up before
OL,20,Fthe war.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1778547792
OL,3,CHouseholds to slam brakes on spending
OL,4,Cas Iran war sends cost surging, warns
OL,5,CEY
OL,7,FGrowth will bounce back to 1.2% in
OL,8,F2027, but this is below the 1.4% pre-
OL,9,Fconflict forecast, according to EY.
OL,11,FIt also warned that growth could
OL,12,Fplunge to just 0.3% this year if the
OL,13,FIran war escalates and the crucial
OL,14,FStrait of Hormuz shipping route
OL,15,Fremains closed for the rest of the
OL,16,Fyear.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1778547792
OL,3,CHouseholds to slam brakes on spending
OL,4,Cas Iran war sends cost surging, warns
OL,5,CEY
OL,7,FInflation will peak at 4% by the end
OL,8,Fof 2026 under its central forecast,
OL,9,Fwhich it believes will see interest
OL,10,Frates held at 3.75% for the rest of
OL,11,Fthe year, while unemployment will hit
OL,12,F5.8% as weaker growth impacts hiring.
OL,14,FThe gloomy report comes ahead of
OL,15,Fofficial gross domestic product (GDP)
OL,16,Ffigures on Thursday, which most
OL,17,Feconomists expect will show the
OL,18,Feconomy slamming into reverse in
OL,19,FMarch, with a 0.2% contraction
OL,20,Ffollowing 0.5% growth in February.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1778547792
OL,3,CHouseholds to slam brakes on spending
OL,4,Cas Iran war sends cost surging, warns
OL,5,CEY
OL,7,FHowever, the outturn for the quarter
OL,8,Fas a whole is set to have been boosted
OL,9,Fby the performance in the first two
OL,10,Fmonths of the year, with economists
OL,11,Fpencilling in 0.6% growth between
OL,12,FJanuary and March.
OL,14,FPeter Arnold, EY's UK chief economist,
OL,15,Fsaid: "Despite a relatively strong
OL,16,Fstart to 2026, the conflict in the
OL,17,FMiddle East means the UK economy is
OL,18,Fonce again being shaped by external
OL,19,Fshocks and on track for another year
OL,20,Fof subdued growth.
OL,26,@wD@GOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1778547792
OL,3,CHouseholds to slam brakes on spending
OL,4,Cas Iran war sends cost surging, warns
OL,5,CEY
OL,7,F"We expect the first quarter of this
OL,8,Fyear to show GDP on a fairly promising
OL,9,Ftrajectory, before flatlining in the
OL,10,Fsecond quarter and gradually
OL,11,Frecovering into 2027 as the global
OL,12,Fmarkets adjust.
OL,14,F"Energy supply constraints will push
OL,15,Finflation higher and delay interest
OL,16,Frate cuts, increasing the cost of
OL,17,Fborrowing for businesses and prompting
OL,18,Fsome companies to reassess spending
OL,19,Fdecisions."
OL,26,@oD@AOUvD@AOU{D@KO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1778547792
OL,3,CHouseholds to slam brakes on spending
OL,4,Cas Iran war sends cost surging, warns
OL,5,CEY
OL,7,FHe added: "Cautious levels of consumer
OL,8,Fspending seen since the pandemic also
OL,9,Fnow appear more structural than
OL,10,Ftemporary, with all income groups
OL,11,Freallocating household spending
OL,12,Ftowards savings and essentials and
OL,13,Faway from discretionary spending.
OL,15,F"This is a concerning trend for
OL,16,Fconsumer-facing sectors and will
OL,17,Flikely be exacerbated by ongoing
OL,18,Fglobal uncertainty and the predicted
OL,19,Frise in inflation."
OL,26,@oD@KOUwD@AOU{D@SO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30408
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1778547792
OL,3,CHouseholds to slam brakes on spending
OL,4,Cas Iran war sends cost surging, warns
OL,5,CEY
OL,7,FOver the next five to 10 years, the
OL,8,Flatest energy supply shock is
OL,9,Fpredicted to cause a 2.2% drop in
OL,10,Feconomic output across UK heavy
OL,11,Fmanufacturing and 1.8% fall for energy
OL,12,Futilities amid a switch to less energy
OL,13,Fintensive areas of the economy.
OL,15,FGrowth will also suffer a 0.3% hit to
OL,16,Flong-term output in consumer services,
OL,17,Fsuch as retail, hospitality and events.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30409
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1778547792
OL,3,CHouseholds to slam brakes on spending
OL,4,Cas Iran war sends cost surging, warns
OL,5,CEY
OL,7,FMr Arnold said: "Industrial and
OL,8,Fconsumer-facing businesses are
OL,9,Fparticularly exposed to the effects of
OL,10,Fenergy volatility.
OL,12,F"High electricity prices were already
OL,13,Fconstraining UK economic output last
OL,14,Fyear, and further energy market
OL,15,Fdisruption will intensify this
OL,16,Fpressure."
OL,26,@oD@QOUtD@AOUxD@JO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/9
